{"orig":"/Users/kalaverin/src/lang/nim/lib/pure/algorithm.nim","nimble":"stdlib","moduleDescription":"This module implements some common generic algorithms on <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">openArray</span></span></tt>s.\n<h1><a class=\"toc-backref\" id=\"basic-usage\" href=\"#basic-usage\">Basic usage</a></h1>\n<h1><a class=\"toc-backref\" id=\"see-also\" href=\"#see-also\">See also</a></h1><ul class=\"simple\"><li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"sequtils.html\">sequtils module</a> for working with the built-in seq type</li>\n<li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"tables.html\">tables module</a> for sorting tables</li>\n</ul>\n","entries":[{"name":"SortOrder","type":"skType","line":52,"col":13,"code":"SortOrder = enum\n  Descending, Ascending"},{"name":"`*`","type":"skProc","line":55,"col":0,"code":"proc `*`(x: int; order: SortOrder): int {.inline, raises: [], tags: [],\n    forbids: [].}","signature":{"return":"int","arguments":[{"name":"x","type":"int"},{"name":"order","type":"SortOrder"}],"pragmas":["inline","raises: []","tags: []","forbids: []"]},"description":"<p>Flips the sign of <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">x</span></span></tt> if <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">order</span> <span class=\"Operator\">==</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">Descending</span></span></tt>. If <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">order</span> <span class=\"Operator\">==</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">Ascending</span></span></tt> then <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">x</span></span></tt> is returned.</p>\n<p><tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">x</span></span></tt> is supposed to be the result of a comparator, i.e.<p><tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Operator\">&lt;</span> <span class=\"DecNumber\">0</span></span></tt> for <em>less than</em>,<br/><tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Operator\">==</span> <span class=\"DecNumber\">0</span></span></tt> for <em>equal</em>,<br/><tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Operator\">&gt;</span> <span class=\"DecNumber\">0</span></span></tt> for <em>greater than</em>.<br/></p></p>\n"},{"name":"fill","type":"skProc","line":77,"col":0,"code":"proc fill[T](a: var openArray[T]; first, last: Natural; value: T)","signature":{"arguments":[{"name":"a","type":"var openArray[T]"},{"name":"first","type":"Natural"},{"name":"last","type":"Natural"},{"name":"value","type":"T"}],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"<p>Assigns <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">value</span></span></tt> to all elements of the slice <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">a</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"Identifier\">first</span><span class=\"Operator\">..</span><span class=\"Identifier\">last</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">]</span></span></tt>.</p>\n<p>If an invalid range is passed, it raises <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">IndexDefect</span></span></tt>.</p>\n"},{"name":"fill","type":"skProc","line":90,"col":0,"code":"proc fill[T](a: var openArray[T]; value: T)","signature":{"arguments":[{"name":"a","type":"var openArray[T]"},{"name":"value","type":"T"}],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"Assigns <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">value</span></span></tt> to all elements of the container <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">a</span></span></tt>."},{"name":"reverse","type":"skProc","line":101,"col":0,"code":"proc reverse[T](a: var openArray[T]; first, last: Natural)","signature":{"arguments":[{"name":"a","type":"var openArray[T]"},{"name":"first","type":"Natural"},{"name":"last","type":"Natural"}],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"<p>Reverses the slice <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">a</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"Identifier\">first</span><span class=\"Operator\">..</span><span class=\"Identifier\">last</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">]</span></span></tt>.</p>\n<p>If an invalid range is passed, it raises <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">IndexDefect</span></span></tt>.</p>\n<p><strong>See also:</strong></p>\n<ul class=\"simple\"><li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#reversed,openArray[T],Natural,int\">reversed proc</a> reverse a slice and returns a <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">seq</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"Identifier\">T</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">]</span></span></tt></li>\n<li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#reversed,openArray[T]\">reversed proc</a> reverse and returns a <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">seq</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"Identifier\">T</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">]</span></span></tt></li>\n</ul>\n"},{"name":"reverse","type":"skProc","line":123,"col":0,"code":"proc reverse[T](a: var openArray[T])","signature":{"arguments":[{"name":"a","type":"var openArray[T]"}],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"<p>Reverses the contents of the container <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">a</span></span></tt>.</p>\n<p><strong>See also:</strong></p>\n<ul class=\"simple\"><li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#reversed,openArray[T],Natural,int\">reversed proc</a> reverse a slice and returns a <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">seq</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"Identifier\">T</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">]</span></span></tt></li>\n<li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#reversed,openArray[T]\">reversed proc</a> reverse and returns a <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">seq</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"Identifier\">T</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">]</span></span></tt></li>\n</ul>\n"},{"name":"reversed","type":"skProc","line":138,"col":0,"code":"proc reversed[T](a: openArray[T]): seq[T] {.inline.}","signature":{"return":"seq[T]","arguments":[{"name":"a","type":"openArray[T]"}],"pragmas":["inline"],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"<p>Returns the elements of <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">a</span></span></tt> in reverse order.</p>\n<p><strong>See also:</strong></p>\n<ul class=\"simple\"><li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#reverse,openArray[T]\">reverse proc</a></li>\n</ul>\n"},{"name":"reversed","type":"skProc","line":150,"col":0,"code":"proc reversed[T](a: openArray[T]; first: Natural; last: int): seq[T] {.inline,\n    deprecated: \"use: `reversed(toOpenArray(a, first, last))`\".}","signature":{"return":"seq[T]","arguments":[{"name":"a","type":"openArray[T]"},{"name":"first","type":"Natural"},{"name":"last","type":"int"}],"pragmas":["inline","deprecated: \"use: `reversed(toOpenArray(a, first, last))`\""],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]}},{"name":"binarySearch","type":"skProc","line":159,"col":0,"code":"proc binarySearch[T, K](a: openArray[T]; key: K;\n                        cmp: proc (x: T; y: K): int {.closure.}): int {.\n    effectsOf: cmp.}","signature":{"return":"int","arguments":[{"name":"a","type":"openArray[T]"},{"name":"key","type":"K"},{"name":"cmp","type":"proc (x: T; y: K): int {.closure.}"}],"pragmas":["effectsOf: cmp"],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"},{"name":"K"}]},"description":"<p>Binary search for <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">key</span></span></tt> in <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">a</span></span></tt>. Return the index of <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">key</span></span></tt> or -1 if not found. Assumes that <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">a</span></span></tt> is sorted according to <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">cmp</span></span></tt>.</p>\n<p><tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">cmp</span></span></tt> is the comparator function to use, the expected return values are the same as those of system.cmp.</p>\n"},{"name":"binarySearch","type":"skProc","line":210,"col":0,"code":"proc binarySearch[T](a: openArray[T]; key: T): int","signature":{"return":"int","arguments":[{"name":"a","type":"openArray[T]"},{"name":"key","type":"T"}],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"Binary search for <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">key</span></span></tt> in <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">a</span></span></tt>. Return the index of <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">key</span></span></tt> or -1 if not found. Assumes that <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">a</span></span></tt> is sorted."},{"name":"lowerBound","type":"skProc","line":221,"col":0,"code":"proc lowerBound[T, K](a: openArray[T]; key: K;\n                      cmp: proc (x: T; k: K): int {.closure.}): int {.\n    effectsOf: cmp.}","signature":{"return":"int","arguments":[{"name":"a","type":"openArray[T]"},{"name":"key","type":"K"},{"name":"cmp","type":"proc (x: T; k: K): int {.closure.}"}],"pragmas":["effectsOf: cmp"],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"},{"name":"K"}]},"description":"<p>Returns the index of the first element in <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">a</span></span></tt> that is not less than (i.e. greater or equal to) <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">key</span></span></tt>, or last if no such element is found. In other words if you have a sorted sequence and you call <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">insert</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"Identifier\">thing</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">elm</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">lowerBound</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"Identifier\">thing</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">elm</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span></span></tt> the sequence will still be sorted. Assumes that <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">a</span></span></tt> is sorted according to <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">cmp</span></span></tt>.</p>\n<p>If an invalid range is passed, it raises <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">IndexDefect</span></span></tt>.</p>\n<p>This version uses <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">cmp</span></span></tt> to compare the elements. The expected return values are the same as those of <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">system</span><span class=\"Operator\">.</span><span class=\"Identifier\">cmp</span></span></tt>.</p>\n<p><strong>See also:</strong></p>\n<ul class=\"simple\"><li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#upperBound,openArray[T],K,proc(T,K)\">upperBound proc</a> sorted by <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">cmp</span></span></tt> in the specified order</li>\n<li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#upperBound,openArray[T],T\">upperBound proc</a></li>\n</ul>\n"},{"name":"lowerBound","type":"skProc","line":257,"col":0,"code":"proc lowerBound[T](a: openArray[T]; key: T): int","signature":{"return":"int","arguments":[{"name":"a","type":"openArray[T]"},{"name":"key","type":"T"}],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"<p>Returns the index of the first element in <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">a</span></span></tt> that is not less than (i.e. greater or equal to) <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">key</span></span></tt>, or last if no such element is found. In other words if you have a sorted sequence and you call <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">insert</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"Identifier\">thing</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">elm</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">lowerBound</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"Identifier\">thing</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">elm</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span></span></tt> the sequence will still be sorted. Assumes that <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">a</span></span></tt> is sorted.</p>\n<p>This version uses the default comparison function <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">cmp</span></span></tt>.</p>\n<p><strong>See also:</strong></p>\n<ul class=\"simple\"><li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#upperBound,openArray[T],K,proc(T,K)\">upperBound proc</a> sorted by <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">cmp</span></span></tt> in the specified order</li>\n<li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#upperBound,openArray[T],T\">upperBound proc</a></li>\n</ul>\n"},{"name":"upperBound","type":"skProc","line":271,"col":0,"code":"proc upperBound[T, K](a: openArray[T]; key: K;\n                      cmp: proc (x: T; k: K): int {.closure.}): int {.\n    effectsOf: cmp.}","signature":{"return":"int","arguments":[{"name":"a","type":"openArray[T]"},{"name":"key","type":"K"},{"name":"cmp","type":"proc (x: T; k: K): int {.closure.}"}],"pragmas":["effectsOf: cmp"],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"},{"name":"K"}]},"description":"<p>Returns the index of the first element in <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">a</span></span></tt> that is greater than <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">key</span></span></tt>, or last if no such element is found. In other words if you have a sorted sequence and you call <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">insert</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"Identifier\">thing</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">elm</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">upperBound</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"Identifier\">thing</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">elm</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span></span></tt> the sequence will still be sorted. Assumes that <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">a</span></span></tt> is sorted according to <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">cmp</span></span></tt>.</p>\n<p>If an invalid range is passed, it raises <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">IndexDefect</span></span></tt>.</p>\n<p>This version uses <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">cmp</span></span></tt> to compare the elements. The expected return values are the same as those of <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">system</span><span class=\"Operator\">.</span><span class=\"Identifier\">cmp</span></span></tt>.</p>\n<p><strong>See also:</strong></p>\n<ul class=\"simple\"><li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#lowerBound,openArray[T],K,proc(T,K)\">lowerBound proc</a> sorted by <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">cmp</span></span></tt> in the specified order</li>\n<li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#lowerBound,openArray[T],T\">lowerBound proc</a></li>\n</ul>\n"},{"name":"upperBound","type":"skProc","line":307,"col":0,"code":"proc upperBound[T](a: openArray[T]; key: T): int","signature":{"return":"int","arguments":[{"name":"a","type":"openArray[T]"},{"name":"key","type":"T"}],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"<p>Returns the index of the first element in <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">a</span></span></tt> that is greater than <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">key</span></span></tt>, or last if no such element is found. In other words if you have a sorted sequence and you call <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">insert</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"Identifier\">thing</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">elm</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">upperBound</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"Identifier\">thing</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">elm</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span></span></tt> the sequence will still be sorted. Assumes that <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">a</span></span></tt> is sorted.</p>\n<p>This version uses the default comparison function <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">cmp</span></span></tt>.</p>\n<p><strong>See also:</strong></p>\n<ul class=\"simple\"><li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#lowerBound,openArray[T],K,proc(T,K)\">lowerBound proc</a> sorted by <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">cmp</span></span></tt> in the specified order</li>\n<li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#lowerBound,openArray[T],T\">lowerBound proc</a></li>\n</ul>\n"},{"name":"sort","type":"skProc","line":368,"col":0,"code":"func sort[T](a: var openArray[T]; cmp: proc (x, y: T): int {.closure.};\n             order = SortOrder.Ascending) {.effectsOf: cmp.}","signature":{"arguments":[{"name":"a","type":"var openArray[T]"},{"name":"cmp","type":"proc (x, y: T): int {.closure.}"},{"name":"order","type":"","default":"SortOrder.Ascending"}],"pragmas":["effectsOf: cmp"],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"<p>Default Nim sort (an implementation of merge sort). The sorting is guaranteed to be stable (that is, equal elements stay in the same order) and the worst case is guaranteed to be O(n log n). Sorts by <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">cmp</span></span></tt> in the specified <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">order</span></span></tt>.</p>\n<p>The current implementation uses an iterative mergesort to achieve this. It uses a temporary sequence of length <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">a</span><span class=\"Operator\">.</span><span class=\"Identifier\">len</span> <span class=\"Keyword\">div</span> <span class=\"DecNumber\">2</span></span></tt>. If you do not wish to provide your own <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">cmp</span></span></tt>, you may use <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">system</span><span class=\"Operator\">.</span><span class=\"Identifier\">cmp</span></span></tt> or instead call the overloaded version of <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">sort</span></span></tt>, which uses <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">system</span><span class=\"Operator\">.</span><span class=\"Identifier\">cmp</span></span></tt>.</p>\n<p><pre class=\"listing\"><span class=\"Identifier\">sort</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"Identifier\">myIntArray</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">system</span><span class=\"Operator\">.</span><span class=\"Identifier\">cmp</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"Identifier\">int</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"Comment\"># do not use cmp[string] here as we want to use the specialized</span>\n<span class=\"Comment\"># overload:</span>\n<span class=\"Identifier\">sort</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"Identifier\">myStrArray</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">system</span><span class=\"Operator\">.</span><span class=\"Identifier\">cmp</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span></pre></p>\n<p>You can inline adhoc comparison procs with the <a class=\"reference external\" href=\"manual.html#procedures-do-notation\">do notation</a>. Example:</p>\n<p><pre class=\"listing\"><span class=\"Identifier\">people</span><span class=\"Operator\">.</span><span class=\"Identifier\">sort</span> <span class=\"Keyword\">do</span> <span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"Identifier\">x</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">y</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">Person</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"Operator\">-&gt;</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">int</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">:</span>\n  <span class=\"Identifier\">result</span> <span class=\"Operator\">=</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">cmp</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"Identifier\">x</span><span class=\"Operator\">.</span><span class=\"Identifier\">surname</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">y</span><span class=\"Operator\">.</span><span class=\"Identifier\">surname</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span>\n  <span class=\"Keyword\">if</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">result</span> <span class=\"Operator\">==</span> <span class=\"DecNumber\">0</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">:</span>\n    <span class=\"Identifier\">result</span> <span class=\"Operator\">=</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">cmp</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"Identifier\">x</span><span class=\"Operator\">.</span><span class=\"Identifier\">name</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">y</span><span class=\"Operator\">.</span><span class=\"Identifier\">name</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span></pre></p>\n<p><strong>See also:</strong></p>\n<ul class=\"simple\"><li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#sort,openArray[T]\">sort proc</a></li>\n<li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#sorted,openArray[T],proc(T,T)\">sorted proc</a> sorted by <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">cmp</span></span></tt> in the specified order</li>\n<li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#sorted,openArray[T]\">sorted proc</a></li>\n<li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#sortedByIt.t,untyped,untyped\">sortedByIt template</a></li>\n</ul>\n"},{"name":"sort","type":"skProc","line":421,"col":0,"code":"proc sort[T](a: var openArray[T]; order = SortOrder.Ascending)","signature":{"arguments":[{"name":"a","type":"var openArray[T]"},{"name":"order","type":"","default":"SortOrder.Ascending"}],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"<p>Shortcut version of <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">sort</span></span></tt> that uses <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">system</span><span class=\"Operator\">.</span><span class=\"Identifier\">cmp</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"Identifier\">T</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">]</span></span></tt> as the comparison function.</p>\n<p><strong>See also:</strong></p>\n<ul class=\"simple\"><li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#sort,openArray[T],proc(T,T)\">sort func</a></li>\n<li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#sorted,openArray[T],proc(T,T)\">sorted proc</a> sorted by <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">cmp</span></span></tt> in the specified order</li>\n<li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#sorted,openArray[T]\">sorted proc</a></li>\n<li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#sortedByIt.t,untyped,untyped\">sortedByIt template</a></li>\n</ul>\n"},{"name":"sorted","type":"skProc","line":431,"col":0,"code":"proc sorted[T](a: openArray[T]; cmp: proc (x, y: T): int {.closure.};\n               order = SortOrder.Ascending): seq[T] {.effectsOf: cmp.}","signature":{"return":"seq[T]","arguments":[{"name":"a","type":"openArray[T]"},{"name":"cmp","type":"proc (x, y: T): int {.closure.}"},{"name":"order","type":"","default":"SortOrder.Ascending"}],"pragmas":["effectsOf: cmp"],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"<p>Returns <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">a</span></span></tt> sorted by <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">cmp</span></span></tt> in the specified <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">order</span></span></tt>.</p>\n<p><strong>See also:</strong></p>\n<ul class=\"simple\"><li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#sort,openArray[T],proc(T,T)\">sort func</a></li>\n<li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#sort,openArray[T]\">sort proc</a></li>\n<li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#sortedByIt.t,untyped,untyped\">sortedByIt template</a></li>\n</ul>\n"},{"name":"sorted","type":"skProc","line":453,"col":0,"code":"proc sorted[T](a: openArray[T]; order = SortOrder.Ascending): seq[T]","signature":{"return":"seq[T]","arguments":[{"name":"a","type":"openArray[T]"},{"name":"order","type":"","default":"SortOrder.Ascending"}],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"<p>Shortcut version of <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">sorted</span></span></tt> that uses <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">system</span><span class=\"Operator\">.</span><span class=\"Identifier\">cmp</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"Identifier\">T</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">]</span></span></tt> as the comparison function.</p>\n<p><strong>See also:</strong></p>\n<ul class=\"simple\"><li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#sort,openArray[T],proc(T,T)\">sort func</a></li>\n<li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#sort,openArray[T]\">sort proc</a></li>\n<li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#sortedByIt.t,untyped,untyped\">sortedByIt template</a></li>\n</ul>\n"},{"name":"sortedByIt","type":"skTemplate","line":471,"col":0,"code":"template sortedByIt(seq1, op: untyped): untyped","signature":{"return":"untyped","arguments":[{"name":"seq1","type":"untyped"},{"name":"op","type":"untyped"}]},"description":"<p>Convenience template around the <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">sorted</span></span></tt> proc to reduce typing.</p>\n<p>The template injects the <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">it</span></span></tt> variable which you can use directly in an expression.</p>\n<p>Because the underlying <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">cmp</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span></span></tt> is defined for tuples you can also do a nested sort.</p>\n<p><strong>See also:</strong></p>\n<ul class=\"simple\"><li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#sort,openArray[T],proc(T,T)\">sort func</a></li>\n<li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#sort,openArray[T]\">sort proc</a></li>\n<li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#sorted,openArray[T],proc(T,T)\">sorted proc</a> sorted by <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">cmp</span></span></tt> in the specified order</li>\n<li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#sorted,openArray[T]\">sorted proc</a></li>\n</ul>\n"},{"name":"isSorted","type":"skProc","line":507,"col":0,"code":"func isSorted[T](a: openArray[T]; cmp: proc (x, y: T): int {.closure.};\n                 order = SortOrder.Ascending): bool {.effectsOf: cmp.}","signature":{"return":"bool","arguments":[{"name":"a","type":"openArray[T]"},{"name":"cmp","type":"proc (x, y: T): int {.closure.}"},{"name":"order","type":"","default":"SortOrder.Ascending"}],"pragmas":["effectsOf: cmp"],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"<p>Checks to see whether <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">a</span></span></tt> is already sorted in <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">order</span></span></tt> using <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">cmp</span></span></tt> for the comparison. The parameters are identical to <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">sort</span></span></tt>. Requires O(n) time.</p>\n<p><strong>See also:</strong></p>\n<ul class=\"simple\"><li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#isSorted,openArray[T]\">isSorted proc</a></li>\n</ul>\n"},{"name":"isSorted","type":"skProc","line":534,"col":0,"code":"proc isSorted[T](a: openArray[T]; order = SortOrder.Ascending): bool","signature":{"return":"bool","arguments":[{"name":"a","type":"openArray[T]"},{"name":"order","type":"","default":"SortOrder.Ascending"}],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"<p>Shortcut version of <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">isSorted</span></span></tt> that uses <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">system</span><span class=\"Operator\">.</span><span class=\"Identifier\">cmp</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"Identifier\">T</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">]</span></span></tt> as the comparison function.</p>\n<p><strong>See also:</strong></p>\n<ul class=\"simple\"><li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#isSorted,openArray[T],proc(T,T)\">isSorted func</a></li>\n</ul>\n"},{"name":"merge","type":"skProc","line":554,"col":0,"code":"proc merge[T](result: var seq[T]; x, y: openArray[T];\n              cmp: proc (x, y: T): int {.closure.}) {.effectsOf: cmp.}","signature":{"arguments":[{"name":"result","type":"var seq[T]"},{"name":"x","type":"openArray[T]"},{"name":"y","type":"openArray[T]"},{"name":"cmp","type":"proc (x, y: T): int {.closure.}"}],"pragmas":["effectsOf: cmp"],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"Merges two sorted <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">openArray</span></span></tt>. <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">x</span></span></tt> and <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">y</span></span></tt> are assumed to be sorted. If you do not wish to provide your own <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">cmp</span></span></tt>, you may use <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">system</span><span class=\"Operator\">.</span><span class=\"Identifier\">cmp</span></span></tt> or instead call the overloaded version of <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">merge</span></span></tt>, which uses <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">system</span><span class=\"Operator\">.</span><span class=\"Identifier\">cmp</span></span></tt>.<div class=\"admonition admonition-info\"><span class=\"admonition-info-text\"><b>Note:</b></span>\nThe original data of <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">result</span></span></tt> is not cleared, new data is appended to <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">result</span></span></tt>.</div>\n<p><strong>See also:</strong></p>\n<ul class=\"simple\"><li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#merge,seq[T],openArray[T],openArray[T]\">merge proc</a></li>\n</ul>\n"},{"name":"merge","type":"skProc","line":631,"col":0,"code":"proc merge[T](result: var seq[T]; x, y: openArray[T]) {.inline.}","signature":{"arguments":[{"name":"result","type":"var seq[T]"},{"name":"x","type":"openArray[T]"},{"name":"y","type":"openArray[T]"}],"pragmas":["inline"],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"<p>Shortcut version of <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">merge</span></span></tt> that uses <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">system</span><span class=\"Operator\">.</span><span class=\"Identifier\">cmp</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"Identifier\">T</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">]</span></span></tt> as the comparison function.</p>\n<p><strong>See also:</strong></p>\n<ul class=\"simple\"><li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#merge,seq[T],openArray[T],openArray[T],proc(T,T)\">merge proc</a></li>\n</ul>\n"},{"name":"product","type":"skProc","line":646,"col":0,"code":"proc product[T](x: openArray[seq[T]]): seq[seq[T]]","signature":{"return":"seq[seq[T]]","arguments":[{"name":"x","type":"openArray[seq[T]]"}],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"Produces the Cartesian product of the array. Every element of the result is a combination of one element from each seq in <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">x</span></span></tt>, with the ith element coming from <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">x</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"Identifier\">i</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">]</span></span></tt>.<div class=\"admonition admonition-warning\"><span class=\"admonition-warning-text\"><b>Warning:</b></span>\ncomplexity may explode.</div>\n"},{"name":"nextPermutation","type":"skProc","line":683,"col":0,"code":"proc nextPermutation[T](x: var openArray[T]): bool {.discardable.}","signature":{"return":"bool","arguments":[{"name":"x","type":"var openArray[T]"}],"pragmas":["discardable"],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"<p>Calculates the next lexicographic permutation, directly modifying <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">x</span></span></tt>. The result is whether a permutation happened, otherwise we have reached the last-ordered permutation.</p>\n<p>If you start with an unsorted array/seq, the repeated permutations will <strong>not</strong> give you all permutations but stop with the last.</p>\n<p><strong>See also:</strong></p>\n<ul class=\"simple\"><li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#prevPermutation,openArray[T]\">prevPermutation proc</a></li>\n</ul>\n"},{"name":"prevPermutation","type":"skProc","line":723,"col":0,"code":"proc prevPermutation[T](x: var openArray[T]): bool {.discardable.}","signature":{"return":"bool","arguments":[{"name":"x","type":"var openArray[T]"}],"pragmas":["discardable"],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"<p>Calculates the previous lexicographic permutation, directly modifying <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">x</span></span></tt>. The result is whether a permutation happened, otherwise we have reached the first-ordered permutation.</p>\n<p><strong>See also:</strong></p>\n<ul class=\"simple\"><li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#nextPermutation,openArray[T]\">nextPermutation proc</a></li>\n</ul>\n"},{"name":"rotateLeft","type":"skProc","line":812,"col":0,"code":"proc rotateLeft[T](arg: var openArray[T]; slice: HSlice[int, int]; dist: int): int {.\n    discardable.}","signature":{"return":"int","arguments":[{"name":"arg","type":"var openArray[T]"},{"name":"slice","type":"HSlice[int, int]"},{"name":"dist","type":"int"}],"pragmas":["discardable"],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"Performs a left rotation on a range of elements. If you want to rotate right, use a negative <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">dist</span></span></tt>. Specifically, <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">rotateLeft</span></span></tt> rotates the elements at <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">slice</span></span></tt> by <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">dist</span></span></tt> positions.<p>The element at index <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">slice</span><span class=\"Operator\">.</span><span class=\"Identifier\">a</span> <span class=\"Operator\">+</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">dist</span></span></tt> will be at index <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">slice</span><span class=\"Operator\">.</span><span class=\"Identifier\">a</span></span></tt>.<br/>The element at index <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">slice</span><span class=\"Operator\">.</span><span class=\"Identifier\">b</span></span></tt> will be at <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">slice</span><span class=\"Operator\">.</span><span class=\"Identifier\">a</span> <span class=\"Operator\">+</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">dist</span> <span class=\"Operator\">-</span> <span class=\"DecNumber\">1</span></span></tt>.<br/>The element at index <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">slice</span><span class=\"Operator\">.</span><span class=\"Identifier\">a</span></span></tt> will be at <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">slice</span><span class=\"Operator\">.</span><span class=\"Identifier\">b</span> <span class=\"Operator\">+</span> <span class=\"DecNumber\">1</span> <span class=\"Operator\">-</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">dist</span></span></tt>.<br/>The element at index <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">slice</span><span class=\"Operator\">.</span><span class=\"Identifier\">a</span> <span class=\"Operator\">+</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">dist</span> <span class=\"Operator\">-</span> <span class=\"DecNumber\">1</span></span></tt> will be at <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">slice</span><span class=\"Operator\">.</span><span class=\"Identifier\">b</span></span></tt>.<br/></p><p>Elements outside of <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">slice</span></span></tt> will be left unchanged. The time complexity is linear to <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">slice</span><span class=\"Operator\">.</span><span class=\"Identifier\">b</span> <span class=\"Operator\">-</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">slice</span><span class=\"Operator\">.</span><span class=\"Identifier\">a</span> <span class=\"Operator\">+</span> <span class=\"DecNumber\">1</span></span></tt>. If an invalid range (<tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">HSlice</span></span></tt>) is passed, it raises <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">IndexDefect</span></span></tt>.</p>\n<dl class=\"docutils\"><dt><tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">slice</span></span></tt></dt>\n<dd>The indices of the element range that should be rotated.</dd>\n<dt><tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">dist</span></span></tt></dt>\n<dd>The distance in amount of elements that the data should be rotated. Can be negative, can be any number.</dd>\n</dl>\n<p><strong>See also:</strong></p>\n<ul class=\"simple\"><li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#rotateLeft,openArray[T],int\">rotateLeft proc</a> for a version which rotates the whole container</li>\n<li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#rotatedLeft,openArray[T],HSlice[int,int],int\">rotatedLeft proc</a> for a version which returns a <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">seq</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"Identifier\">T</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">]</span></span></tt></li>\n</ul>\n"},{"name":"rotateLeft","type":"skProc","line":850,"col":0,"code":"proc rotateLeft[T](arg: var openArray[T]; dist: int): int {.discardable.}","signature":{"return":"int","arguments":[{"name":"arg","type":"var openArray[T]"},{"name":"dist","type":"int"}],"pragmas":["discardable"],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"<p>Same as <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">rotateLeft</span></span></tt>, but with default arguments for slice, so that this procedure operates on the entire <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">arg</span></span></tt>, and not just on a part of it.</p>\n<p><strong>See also:</strong></p>\n<ul class=\"simple\"><li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#rotateLeft,openArray[T],HSlice[int,int],int\">rotateLeft proc</a> for a version which rotates a range</li>\n<li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#rotatedLeft,openArray[T],int\">rotatedLeft proc</a> for a version which returns a <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">seq</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"Identifier\">T</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">]</span></span></tt></li>\n</ul>\n"},{"name":"rotatedLeft","type":"skProc","line":870,"col":0,"code":"proc rotatedLeft[T](arg: openArray[T]; slice: HSlice[int, int]; dist: int): seq[\n    T]","signature":{"return":"seq[T]","arguments":[{"name":"arg","type":"openArray[T]"},{"name":"slice","type":"HSlice[int, int]"},{"name":"dist","type":"int"}],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"<p>Same as <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">rotateLeft</span></span></tt>, just with the difference that it does not modify the argument. It creates a new <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">seq</span></span></tt> instead.</p>\n<p>Elements outside of <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">slice</span></span></tt> will be left unchanged. If an invalid range (<tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">HSlice</span></span></tt>) is passed, it raises <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">IndexDefect</span></span></tt>.</p>\n<dl class=\"docutils\"><dt><tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">slice</span></span></tt></dt>\n<dd>The indices of the element range that should be rotated.</dd>\n<dt><tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">dist</span></span></tt></dt>\n<dd>The distance in amount of elements that the data should be rotated. Can be negative, can be any number.</dd>\n</dl>\n<p><strong>See also:</strong></p>\n<ul class=\"simple\"><li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#rotateLeft,openArray[T],HSlice[int,int],int\">rotateLeft proc</a> for the in-place version of this proc</li>\n<li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#rotatedLeft,openArray[T],int\">rotatedLeft proc</a> for a version which rotates the whole container</li>\n</ul>\n"},{"name":"rotatedLeft","type":"skProc","line":900,"col":0,"code":"proc rotatedLeft[T](arg: openArray[T]; dist: int): seq[T]","signature":{"return":"seq[T]","arguments":[{"name":"arg","type":"openArray[T]"},{"name":"dist","type":"int"}],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"<p>Same as <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">rotateLeft</span></span></tt>, just with the difference that it does not modify the argument. It creates a new <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">seq</span></span></tt> instead.</p>\n<p><strong>See also:</strong></p>\n<ul class=\"simple\"><li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#rotateLeft,openArray[T],int\">rotateLeft proc</a> for the in-place version of this proc</li>\n<li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#rotatedLeft,openArray[T],HSlice[int,int],int\">rotatedLeft proc</a> for a version which rotates a range</li>\n</ul>\n"}]}